<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-07-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-07-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="51" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d51">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of Panama</gloss>
                                to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-07-01"><hi rend="italic">July 1,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Government and people of Panama participate in the sorrow of the
                            Government and people of the United States at the death of their eminent
                            Secretary of State, Mr. John Hay.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">M. Amador
                            Guerrero.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>